<p>When I’ve finished being a nerd for the week you may find me taking part in extreme physical challenges such as <a href="http://toughmudder.com" rel="external">Tough Mudder</a> <small>(above)</small>, you could catch me trying out new cocktails in one of the many hipster bars in Manchester’s Northern Quarter, or perhaps even shaking <a href="http://instagram.com/p/oWpa6pmAjk" rel="external">some of</a> <a href="http://instagram.com/p/oWhCTlmAln" rel="external">my own</a>.</p>

<h2>About this site</h2>
<h3>Toolkit &amp; colophon</h3>
<p>This site is hand coded in <a href="http://www.sublimetext.com/2" rel="external">Sublime Text 2</a>, developed using <a href="http://github.com" rel="external">GitHub</a>, <a href="http://bower.io" rel="external">Bower</a>, <a href="http://gruntjs.com" rel="external">Grunt</a>, <a href="http://assemble.io" rel="external">Assemble</a>, <a href="https://github.com/furzeface/sassface" rel="external">SassFace</a> and <a href="http://typekit.com" rel="external">Typekit</a>.</p>

<p>It is built and deployed with <a href="http://travis-ci.org" rel="external">Travis CI</a> and hosted with <a href="http://" rel="external">Amazon Web Services</a>.</p>

<p>For more info on the typefaces used see my <a href="https://typekit.com/colophons/ejo4unf" rel="external">Typekit colophon page</a>.</p>

<h3>All of the badges&hellip;</h3>
<p>The source code for this site is completely minified, uglified and everything for deployment <small>(bits make bytes)</small> but the entire codebase is hosted on <a href="{{package.repository.url}}" rel="external">GitHub</a> for anyone to have a poke around and play - so feel free to have a look, even <a href="{{package.repository.url}}/issues" rel="external">open issues</a> or submit <a href="{{package.repository.url}}/pulls" rel="external">pull requests</a> if you spot a problem!</p>

